This is a great movie, and being a Chicago fan and having lived in Arizona makes it even better. I think this was James William Guercio's only movie but he should have made more. I guess producing music was more appealing to him.

Thanks for keeping this almost unknown film alive.

A great movie indeed. And the first apperance for Nick Nolte (one of the guys in the hippie gang)

The band playing the rock-concert in the movie, are Madura. Another great band from Chicago and their album also were produced nby J. W. Guercio
